It's called common courtesy, both of which your guilds lack. It's why laws have to be instated in the first place. Ever hear about the &quot;front porch rule&quot;? When anyone sets foot on your front porch, they're family. I may be Southern, but I'm a hell of a lot more likely to be someone's friend than enemy. I can't say the same for all involved in this thread.<br>
<br>
COMMON COURTESY....<br>
That's what this &quot;list&quot; is about. If you think it's foolish, cumbersome, whatever, fine. Don't follow. But when you jump an entire guild, it WILL come back to you some day. And I hope it does in force. <p><CENTER><IMG SRC=http://home.earthlink.net/~cromin/_uimages/Raalf.gif> <BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36425>Magelo Profile</a></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uquasquetonfyrestrike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quasqueton Fyrestrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Road Kill Cabbie</span><br>  Posts: 274<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/31/02 6:26:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> Just a quick head's up about the &quot;list&quot;.  It's not here... and I hope it never shows up here... cause if it does, it'll turn into the next reservation system... and get trashed as soon as Ravenark, etc pisses someone off in the flame section.<br>
<br>
The &quot;list&quot; is all about clerics in-game, in Skyfire.  If folks want on the &quot;list&quot;, log on and head to SF.  Talk to the clerics there, get to know them, and pull up a seat and keep em company.<br>
<br>
Dont post here, cause it has nothing to do with QQ2, or anyone that posts here.<br>
<br>
Heck, it doesnt even have anything to do with me.  I'm just a foo who thinks it's a great idea... but at the end of the day, my opinion means nothing.<br>
<br>
Ooops... almost forgot... as posted earlier, if anyone camping Rage needs help when he pops, shoot me or anyone in Lor Mani a tell.  We'll help, and can usually have a full mobilization within 10 minutes.<br>
<br>
As far as the nay-sayers and negative people go, ignore em.  Stick to your guns, and to your beliefs.  The high road isnt easy, but it's worth it in the end.<br>
<br>
