</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ubinedina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Binedina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/31/02 8:53:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> As the cleric currently out there (Bennea), maybe I can add a little to this thread.  When I first went out to the &quot;camp,&quot; Fadomil was there and had the &quot;list&quot; of people.  He explained that they had only been jotting down the names of clerics who actually came out and talked to the ones currently there.  I don't think anyone is naive enough to think that the &quot;list&quot; is anything other than an effort to bring some order and civility to a long and often tedious camp.   Bennea actually started &quot;camping&quot; out there when Sassami's turn came -- and it was great having some company.  When he popped for her, I called some LC people, she had people from her guild, as well as some others who had helped earlier, and it went well.  Gruffnoy was next, and it was much the same.  We had exchanged phone numbers so people could take turns sleeping, watching -- whatever.  Anyway, as soon as I called him, his guild, some LC, some ADD, and several others helped out and, again, all went well.<br>
<br>
Bennea is currently waiting, and the list I inherited is as follows:  Bennea; Doclotus; LC cleric; Syllie; Breakdown/Mysses; Fenanan; Feadorn; Batto/Binary; Gwendry.  It's probably safe to assume that some might not be able to take their &quot;turn&quot; and some will be bumped up.  Still, having the names does allow people to plan a bit and get to know and cooperate with people from other guilds.  I would have posted sooner, but didn't know this thread was here, and, as I said, this was really only something I inherited.  I do know people on other servers are doing similar things.  Of course people can choose not to respect it, but I think most of us would rather cooperate and help each other in what has turned out to be a bit of a chore. <br>
<br>
Bennea, 60 cleric<br>
Lotus Cult <p>Binedina Benditas</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ubinedina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Binedina</A> at: 5/31/02 9:28:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ugurunt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gurunt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Dar Knight</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/31/02 11:37:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> Thank you Binedina.  Unlike the other folks here, who want to monopolize the spawn and villify anyone who doesn't bow to thier wishes.... you actually seem to understand what I said.<br>
<br>
It's funny... Raalf, a few DosG folks talk about others having no respect for people and not being able to play nice, while telling me directly &quot;do what I say when I say you can or I'll hate you&quot;.  As is other people in this thread treating thier list as an excuse to monopolize a spawn.  <br>
<br>
Hopefully if a cleric does show up in skyfire for Ragefire, they'll get in contact with someone like Binedina who will treat them with a little respect, and not some self-righteous prick that will try and strongarm and bully them into a system they may not have heard of before zoning in.  Respect works both ways, remember that.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
