 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ugurunt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gurunt</A> at: 5/31/02 12:33:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/utamas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tamas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Dar Knight</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/31/02 1:17:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.terrapinsolutions.com/eq/skull.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> GM shows up and WILL AWARD Ragefire to Cleric (b) FIRST because he was in the zone with SUFFICIENT FORCE FIRST. I'm not saying its right, but it's the rules we must live by. -Gemlin<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Seems pretty simple to me. The ones talking about the sufficient force engagement rules are the ones who'd rush there with exactly the intent of petitioning a GM and invoking that sufficient force rule to kill Ragefire and spare themselves the long camp. If you really don't think it's right, stay the hell away, don't spout the rule and say &quot;well, it's not right, but that's how it is.&quot; It's only how it is because that's how you want to play it. It's not like a Ragefire spawn has a rule that requires immediate mobilization to Skyfire, now does it? You don't have to go there. The only reason that sufficient force rule gets invoked is because selfish guilds rush there and demand that rule be enforced. No GM is going to say &quot;Oh, this guild has more people in the zone, so the spawn is theirs&quot; without being called in. I'm sick of so-called uberguilds petitioning GMs and using the rules to justify their &quot;might makes right&quot; actions when they know what they're doing is wrong. It wouldn't be an incident if these guilds didn't feel compelled to run there and make an issue of it. <br>
<br>
These clerics have come up with a system that works, and members of some of the big guilds only seem to want to discuss how they'd use The Rules to undermine the system. I for one have endured the Ragefire camp under this method, and would support and help anyone abiding by it.<br>
<br>
With the abundance of high end equipment, skills and spells that add mana and mana regen, not to mention existing cleric epics already had in these guilds, I wouldn't think another cleric epic is a big enough deal for the so-called uberguilds anymore to be worth causing such trouble. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=137994">Byttorr Ebonknight</A>      /      <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138042">Tamas Sturmpanzer</A><BR>
Beating Up Frogloks For Their Lunch Money Since 1999<BR>
Voices of Rallos Guild, Quellious</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uacturian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Acturian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Dar Knight</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/31/02 1:43:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> This is to all clerics who are actually out there doing the camp:<br>
<br>
You have my blades and my services to back you. You may call apon me at any time, if I am not busy I will come , even to just say hi. When that bastard spawns, I will be there. <br>
<br>
Being kind isnt fuckin hard people. If you cant be kind to others, please go to hell . You deserve to be there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ugurunt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gurunt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Dar Knight</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/31/02 2:06:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> <br>
&quot;These clerics have come up with a system that works, and members of some of the big guilds only seem to want to discuss how they'd use The Rules to undermine the system.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Does nobody see the inherent logical flaw here?   How is this different than Vis saying &quot;check with us if you want to try to have a shot at Trakanon&quot; 2 years ago?  Only difference I see is, Vis were going by the rules of the game, instead of making rules of their own they expected to supercede them.<br>
<br>
Nobody has done anything, currently Lotus Cult and Wraith have clerics willingly using your system.  My concern is many of you guys are trying to treat yourselves as authority.  <br>
<br>
What if a cleric outside of your system  sits in skyfire for 6 days after your crew kills a ragefire and intends to claim the next spawn?  If they simply don't want to get to the end of the line because they are able and willing to make the camp themselves?  Is it going to be a flameboard-fest and gm drama?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ugemlin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gemlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/31/02 2:39:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> You know I'm getting sick and tired of these people attacking someone just because they are in one of the top guilds of a server.<br>
<br>
Name ONE Ragefire spawn that Vis Maior has come in and taken? NAME ONE. You can't, Our clerics for the majority have their epics and do NOT go to skyfire.<br>
<br>
Next How are we inconsiderate? We make deals with other guilds on the server for spawns. If you don't believe me, ask Lotus Cult. They'll be the first to tell you we work out deals with them.<br>
<br>
My posts on this thread was to point out that no matter what the list a few clerics make on this, it will not help. Simple of a fact that most the people on Quellious <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> DO NOT EVEN READ THIS FORUM</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and therefore will invoke the Play Nice Policy rules with GMs when it comes to a contested spawn. I am/was trying to point out a list will NOT work on Everquest due to the nature of people. And Yes a GM <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> WILL</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> award a spawn to anyone who is there FIRST with <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> SUFFICIENT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> force. If you don't believe me, again Ask Lotus Cult, Wraith, Rel In Por, etc. <br>
<br>
Attacking me on this is in poor taste. I'm not even a cleric, but a individual that can see a MAJOR flaw in trying to get a list going here. There will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ALWAYS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be jerks on a server and theres nothing you can do about it. The way Verant has set up the Play Nice Policy on a Blue server severly benifits trolls/jerks/slimeballs/etc..<br>
<br>
The REASON why verant says &quot;SUFFICIENT FORCE&quot; is to stop guilds from sending one person to every spawn that that guild wants to hit and claim it camped. <br>
<br>
Is there a solution to Ragefire problems? In my opinion Yes.<br>
<br>
Simple put the Ragefire spawn on like the 4th or 5th island in the plane of air and make him a 24 hour spawn. In this way you will HAVE to have sufficient force to get to him, You will not get a contested spawn battle going (because yes, it takes keys to get to that island and it will be CLEAR on who should get him first). A side benifit would be that this zone would actually be used again. <br>
<br>
Other than something like I meantioned, the ONLY solution now is to have 12-16 of your friends camp ragefire with you. This will insure if he pops that you will get ragefire awarded to you.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uwhytspirit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whytspirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Of the Nexus</span><br>  Posts: 310<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/31/02 2:50:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> OK, time to add in my words again. A couple important things seem to have been missed by the naysayers. One was already pointed out. It is a way of handling the spawn IN game between clerics IN game. I too hope this list never hits the boards as something official. What we have here is NOT a cut and dried system, but a fellowship of clerics, their guilds and friends, all lending support to each other to accomplish a common goal. This started out simply when a cleric who wished to camp Ragefire after another cleric was done helped camp Rage, lent support simply for the first to call camp.<br>
<br>
This leads me to a second issue. In the case of a cleric not in &quot;the system&quot; camping Rage at the same time as someone on the &quot;list&quot;. Generally camp is announced every so often, so I would hope that this cleric who was interested in camping Ragefire would object, say &quot;umm, I am too&quot; and go work things out one way or the other. I am not going to spend a lot of time on this issue because most of the objections to the way its being handled and the inherent problems/issues aren't even clerics. <br>
<br>
This whole &quot;system&quot; is not anything formal. The &quot;list&quot; is exactly what was said, indicated interest (further proved by spending time out there as well). The reason this will work is because guild lines are not defined for this purpose necessarily. It is based on honor, respect and the willingness to help others. There is no alliance of guilds controlling this whole thing, contrary to what some of you may seem to think you know. <br>
<br>
Have we had a single spawn issue since this has been done? No, I don't think so. Why? Because folks are banding together for the greater good. Clerics and their friends are putting in the time. Gone are the days when a guild would sit their cleric alone in Skyfire to sit and wait for the human version to spawn and then have to rush into the zone, hopefully before somone else gets word. There are constantly people there, as well as extensive resources to forces that can be brought in quickly. <br>
